reviews.review_text: That ole black magic... I've rarely, if ever, heard a tape that so clearly captures the awe and wonder of Space as this one.  You really feel you're in the music hall, wrapped up in the spell.  Thank you so much for this, Charlie.
... My favorite AUD for this date.
Great recording and show I Just Want To Make Love To You done in the fast style of Caution. Awesome pre drums and drums/space. Whole show definitely worth a listen

Don't forget the Caution Jam There is a Caution jam out of Just Wanna Make Love to You that should be on the song list.  I remember there being some speculation as to their alleged intent to go into the non-performed parts of Terrapin before Samson.  There was a lot of head scratching that night but I think it's really just a little bit of stage confusion about the next song.  There's definitely a Caution jam though.  Great show, second set in particular.  Everyone was clapping and chanting NFA on the way out of the place.  This is the best recording too.

Really nice recording, thanks to those that did! As a result, I could dose myself "to the gills" and get inside this stuff! I remember really liking this show, when I had it on tape back in the mid-80s. And, recalling my thoughts at the time... Jerry was trying to saw off the corners of the Centrum... Its not as pronounced now, likely the lack of drugs, but also my ear listens differently to what the boys were doing! I hear Caution from Wanna Make Love to you, through the end of Miracle! Not particularly defined, but not a bad extended jam built off those two tunes. likely that is what made me think jerry was sawing corners! But it was a way to think about how the music felt, in that moment, that was valuable to the experience, and here (what almost 40 years!?) later! I find the guys who comment on the shows from the 70s hard to believe... definitely My Issue; but here I am commenting on shit (particularly vivid thoughts and feelings about these shows!) maybe only 8-10 years older/later!

This is my little contribution to the fabric of the universe... must appreciate this as a repository of memories!
